                               EthAddress eth_addr,

        Creates a new Neighbor Discovery client.
        Parameters:
        ip_interface - the IP interface
        ip_addr - the IP address
        eth_addr - the Ethernet address
        arp_table_timeout - ARP table timeout in milliseconds; if greater than 0, the ARP responses are cached in a local ARP table for this amount of time

    • Method Detail

      • request

        public EthAddress request(Ip6Address target_ip_addr)
        Gets the Ethernet address of a target IP address. It sends a ICMP6 Neighbor Solicitation request for the given IP address and captures the Neighbor Advertisement response.

        This is a blocking method. It waits for a response and returns only when a response is received or the maximum number of attempts occurred.

        Parameters:
        target_ip_addr - the target IP address
        Returns:
        the requested Ethernet address, or null in case of failure

      • lookup

        public EthAddress lookup(Ip6Address target_ip_addr)
        Gets the Ethernet address of a target IP address. It first looks into a local ARP table; if the address is not found, a ARP request is sent.
        Parameters:
        target_ip_addr - the IP address
        Returns:
        the requested Ethernet address, or null in case of failure

        eth_addr - the corresponding Ethernet address
